            "body": "<a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"P2\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p2.svg?v=9\" align=\"top\"></a> **String-scan boundary check is susceptible to false positives from comments and doc strings**\n\n`source.contains(import)` matches any occurrence of the forbidden string in the file, including in comments (e.g. `// previously called crate::state::live_tree`) or string literals. A developer adding a migration comment or doc reference to a git-layer module would trigger a spurious test failure, with no indication that it came from prose rather than an actual `use` item. A narrower check that matches only at the start of a `use` statement \u2014 e.g. filtering lines that start with `use ` or checking for `use crate::git` \u2014 would eliminate that class of false positive.\n\n<a href=\"https://app.greptile.com/api/ide/codex?prompt=IMPORTANT%3A%20Work%20in%20the%20repository%20%22adamblumoff%2Fscope-vcs%22%20on%20the%20existing%20branch%20%22codex%2Fstaged-push-domain-boundary%22.%20Checkout%20that%20branch%20%E2%80%94%20do%20NOT%20create%20a%20new%20branch%20or%20open%20a%20new%20PR.%20Push%20your%20changes%20to%20%22codex%2Fstaged-push-domain-boundary%22.%0A%0AThis%20is%20a%20comment%20left%20during%20a%20code%20review.%0APath%3A%20api%2Ftests%2Fdomain_boundary.rs%0ALine%3A%2021-24%0A%0AComment%3A%0A**String-scan%20boundary%20check%20is%20susceptible%20to%20false%20positives%20from%20comments%20and%20doc%20strings**%0A%0A%60source.contains%28import%29%60%20matches%20any%20occurrence%20of%20the%20forbidden%20string%20in%20the%20file%2C%20including%20in%20comments%20%28e.g.%20%60%2F%2F%20previously%20called%20crate%3A%3Astate%3A%3Alive_tree%60%29%20or%20string%20literals.%20A%20developer%20adding%20a%20migration%20comment%20or%20doc%20reference%20to%20a%20git-layer%20module%20would%20trigger%20a%20spurious%20test%20failure%2C%20with%20no%20indication%20that%20it%20came%20from%20prose%20rather%20than%20an%20actual%20%60use%60%20