            "id": "PRRC_kwDOS97bAM7QWwG3",
            "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Catch bare outer-layer imports**\n\nThis matcher only looks for forbidden imports followed by `::`, so a domain module can still add `use crate::git;`, `use crate::{git, ...};`, or an alias like `use crate::git as outer_git;` and then call through that local name without leaving any `crate::git::` token for the direct-reference scan. Since this test is meant to enforce the domain boundary, include bare module/alias import forms as violations too.\n\nUseful? React with \ud83d\udc4d\u00a0/ \ud83d\udc4e.",
            "createdAt": "2026-06-30T01:30:41Z",
