            "id": "PRRC_kwDOS97bAM7QWwG7",
            "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Strip char literals before scanning strings**\n\nWhen a domain file contains a double-quote character literal before an outer-layer reference, this branch treats the `\"` inside that char literal as the start of a string and can replace the following `crate::git::...` tokens before the direct-reference scan runs. That lets a file with a quote constant above a forbidden call pass the boundary test, so character literals need to be skipped before normal string handling.\n\nUseful? React with \ud83d\udc4d\u00a0/ \ud83d\udc4e.",
            "createdAt": "2026-06-30T01:30:41Z",
