            "id": "PRRC_kwDOS97bAM7QWwG9",
            "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Reject relative imports to outer layers**\n\nBecause this filter only inspects `use crate::...` statements, a domain module can still import an outer layer with a relative path such as `use super::git::...` from `mod.rs` or `use super::super::git::...` from a child module, then call through that import without any `crate::git::` token in the file. That bypasses the boundary test while still creating the forbidden domain-to-outer dependency, so relative paths that resolve back to the crate root need to be checked too.\n\nUseful? React with \ud83d\udc4d\u00a0/ \ud83d\udc4e.",
            "createdAt": "2026-06-30T01:30:41Z",
