            "id": "PRRC_kwDOS97bAM7QW7pd",
            "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Parse visibility-qualified use statements**\n\nA domain module can add a visibility-qualified import such as `pub(crate) use crate::git as outer_git;` and this collector skips it because it only starts statements whose trimmed line begins with `use `. The direct-reference scan also looks for `crate::git::`, so a bare or aliased re-export of the forbidden module is missed and can then be used through `outer_git::...`, bypassing the boundary test that is meant to enforce no outer-layer imports.\n\nUseful? React with \ud83d\udc4d\u00a0/ \ud83d\udc4e.",
